column2: Were two vowels (lax and tense) selected for the sustained vowels task?
Was the vowel 'i' used during videostroboscopy?
Did the subject vocalize the lax vowel steadily 3 to 5 seconds?
Did the subject vocalize the tense vowel steadily 3 to 5 seconds?
Was the subject provided flash cards one at a time with the targeted sentences?
Did the clinician elicit at least 20 seconds of natural conversational speech using the standard interview questions?
